000033>(8/28/01 12:18:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honest opinions wanted</span><hr size=1> Since, it's easier to speak to 'you' than 'a person,' I am just going to phrase all my answers as if it is you whom is asking.<br>
<br>
a) Move the character and lose all the items on it?<br>
<br>
If you have nothing to do here, why would you have more to do on another server?  It seems to me, as a gut reaction to the context of your question, that the only reason to move a full-fledged character to another server is to escape a reputation...<br>
<br>
If you want to just 'start fresh,' then moving your character seems counterproductive, although maybe people won't notice a naked high-level gathering a new set of gear.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
Why not just start fresh if you're going to move without knowing people on the other server already?  With your knowledge of the game, you should level pretty quickly, and you'll make friends on the way...<br>
<br>
b) Ebay and quit the game entirely?<br>
<br>
That's a descision that can't be made for anyone.  It depends on how you feel about the time you've invested in your character, the reputation you spent your time creating, and, of course, how much you owe on your student loans =P<br>
<br>
c) Try to make things work on the server they are on?<br>
<br>
Personaly, I don't see the value of a) over c), so I'd say it really comes down to b) or c).  From there, I'd redifine the questions as:<br>
<br>
1) Does EQ still have anything to offer you?<br>
<br>
Taking a break is always an option.  Time away from EQ may help you find out if you have anything left to gain by playing...<br>
<br>
Then, if the answer is no,<br>
<br>
2) Do you really want to E-bay?<br>
<br>
As far as e-baying is concerned, I don't really have an issue with people who are selling thier accounts because they're done.  You're done, you served your time, why not use the time you spent camping the AC to pay off a credit card, or take a chunk out of your school loan?  (You can see where my mind is at =)<br>
<br>
The people who give e-bay a horrible name are those who farm-sell-farm-sell-farm-sell.  Let your friends and guild know if you plan on e-baying.  You owe them that much, not only to give them a chance to say goodbye, but also to prevent them from getting scammed by the new player.<br>
<br>
Game, hobby, or addiction, you need to do what keeps you happy.  And I say this not just for your own benefit, but for the benefit of those around you.  If you are unhappy with the game, odds are good you are going to bring the people you play with down as well.<br>
<br>
For a moment, imagine a server where everyone was happy to be there, and happy to be playing.  Then keep in mind that we all play a part in making that server.  <br>
<br>
Shade and Sweet Water,<br>
Hedge <p><img src="http://geoinfo.nmt.edu/staff/rebach/hedgesig.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=6641.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=6636.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=6628.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.threadControl?topicID=6628.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6628.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6628.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqasylumgeneral">General<option value="eqasylumfrm25">Raid Discussions<option value="eqasylumthetavernincharacterdiscussion">The Tavern <option value="eqasylumthemerchantsunionbuyselltradeorannounceyourservicesforhire">The Merchant's Union<option value="eqasylumbiographiessharesomeinfoaboutyourself">Biographies <option value="eqasylumplayerrunquestsorganizeandfindactorsfordynamicquests">Player Run Quests <option value="eqasylumlook